Notebook[{
Cell["mma-hol \[Dash] Runnable Examples", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"4d828d18-1876-4d76-bffd-b2dee32815f5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An LCF-style HOL theorem prover in the Wolfram Language. Evaluate the ",
 "cells top to bottom with Shift+Enter. The first cell loads the prebuilt ",
 "snapshot (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"bootstrap", ".", "mx"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cd2f8fa9-a4fd-4fb0-a28a-81a376ebaa8b"],
 "); if it is missing, run ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"wolframscript", " ", "-", 
   RowBox[{"file", " ", 
    RowBox[{"tests", "/", 
     RowBox[{"build_snapshot", ".", "wls"}]}]}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4328cfec-9806-4861-928b-a9981264bc1a"],
 " in the repo root first."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"970ea14c-b0c4-4c60-b74b-bac2eb6aa1ec"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7f7a3869-3a7c-4512-89da-14f9c997519d"],

Cell["Load the kernel + the full standard library:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2c504b91-2616-4fca-9a4d-1f1d943e0bad"],

Cell["\<\
(* Load the library: Stable mode + restore the prebuilt snapshot. *)
root = ParentDirectory[NotebookDirectory[]];
Global`$HOLEncapsulationMode = \"Stable\";
Get[FileNameJoin[{root, \"bootstrap.mx\"}]];
$ContextPath = Join[
  Select[Contexts[], StringMatchQ[#, \"HOL`*\"] && ! StringContainsQ[#, \
\"Private`\"] &],
  $ContextPath];

(* Display helper: re-print a theorem's outermost universal with a clean \
binder 
   name. The library deliberately uses distinctive (collision-resistant) bound-
   variable names; prettyS only renames for display \[Dash] aconv-identical, \
the 
   library theorem is untouched. *)
prettyS[th_] := With[{ty = concl[th][[2, 1, 2]]}, GEN[mkVar[\"S\", ty], \
SPEC[mkVar[\"S\", ty], th]]];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"37e7e86a-73a5-41e6-8639-a735706fbe88"],

Cell["1. The trusted kernel", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"fac655dc-6a1c-46a8-9bf7-e1da41546163"],

Cell["\<\
Every value of theorem type is built by the 10 primitive rules. formatThm \
renders a theorem as \[RightTee] p.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d164eddf-99d1-4de4-babf-2598c4f17329"],

Cell["formatThm[TRUTH]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"f132a53e-0482-4a5b-803f-2a59e64ad987"],

Cell["2. Propositional automation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"69070881-1805-4a93-9485-15e417f54aaa"],

Cell["\<\
propTaut decides propositional tautologies and returns a kernel-checked \
theorem. parseTerm reads HOL syntax (==> implication, \\/ or, ~ not).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0e2be18c-62d5-4ac8-bc01-74f37c365ac1"],

Cell["formatThm[propTaut[parseTerm[\"p ==> p\"]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"9fa635fa-e45d-4213-b370-686af4983043"],

Cell["formatThm[propTaut[parseTerm[\"p \\\\/ ~p\"]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"e853cc60-9c9f-4e55-b295-5a1a51193143"],

Cell["3. Proving with tactics", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"69bda186-53a9-48f1-86b5-88691f274999"],

Cell["\<\
prove[goal, tactic] runs a tactic against a goal and returns the discharged \
theorem.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f662d28b-4727-4a7d-8476-3f8a95afc28e"],

Cell["formatThm[prove[parseTerm[\"T\"], acceptTac[TRUTH]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a3e65e9a-7247-42dc-8984-676ccae7c3ff"],

Cell["4. The standard library: marquee theorems", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"48597b58-b351-4cd7-9ba2-5b7f231c59a8"],

Cell["\<\
The real numbers are built from Dedekind cuts; these are the proven capstones \
of stdlib/Real/ (all 0-sorry, rechecked by the kernel).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9e0f8eb4-7c44-4486-98ef-257c0e09bdd3"],

Cell["\<\
(* Dedekind completeness: every nonempty bounded-above set has a least upper \
bound *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`dedekindCompleteThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"25c8341a-974b-463b-bb41-0058e5e483f4"],

Cell["\<\
(* Bolzano-Weierstrass *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`bwSequentialThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"8064726a-490f-4de7-b896-f24ee88d63e3"],

Cell["\<\
(* Heine-Borel for a closed interval *)
formatThm[HOL`Stdlib`Real`compactnessPrincipleThm]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"218bdf08-11a6-40fd-ae3a-068f111f98c1"],

Cell["\<\
(* compact <=> sequentially compact (general real sets) *)
formatThm[prettyS[HOL`Stdlib`Real`compactIffSequentialCompactThm]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"f8a748e8-e57a-4a8e-92ff-6f35597e283f"],

Cell["\<\
(* connected <=> interval *)
formatThm[prettyS[HOL`Stdlib`Real`connectedIffIntervalSetThm]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"3b951753-8967-4842-850a-d2f5644f8be8"],

Cell["5. A proof from scratch, checked live", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3599989b-6291-4363-871c-b0cd884cd030"],

Cell["\<\
The cells above only displayed finished theorems. Here we BUILD one: prove \
sets a goal, a tactic discharges it, and the kernel rechecks every step. We \
prove p /\\ q ==> q /\\ p (note the swap).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"56dc1d6d-8e9b-4cb1-a2da-b40f69755434"],

Cell["\<\
goalA = parseTerm[\"p /\\\\ q ==> q /\\\\ p\"];
thmA = prove[goalA,
  THEN[dischTac,
    THENL[conjTac, {
      acceptTac[CONJUNCT2[ASSUME[goalA[[1, 2]]]]],
      acceptTac[CONJUNCT1[ASSUME[goalA[[1, 2]]]]]}]]];
formatThm[thmA]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4a8a1b73-cec3-448e-89f3-0e32a997787e"],

Cell["6. Real analysis, proved automatically", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b6b2da67-9c1d-4b6b-9974-e2dd4a74ba2f"],

Cell["\<\
realArithProve decides linear real arithmetic and emits a Farkas certificate \
the kernel replays. A few builders state the goal as a HOL term (we lift the \
forall/imp constants out of parseTerm to avoid typing Unicode), then the \
prover proves the midpoint inequality  a < b ==> a < (a+b)/2  by itself.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"61cf479f-4e4b-49e0-8470-1074f368c05c"],

Cell["\<\
realTy = mkType[\"real\", {}];
forallName = parseTerm[\"!z. z\"][[1, 1]];
impName = parseTerm[\"a ==> b\"][[1, 1, 1]];
all[v_, body_] := mkComb[mkConst[forallName, tyFun[tyFun[typeOf[v], boolTy], \
boolTy]], mkAbs[v, body]];
imp[p_, q_] := mkComb[mkComb[mkConst[impName, tyFun[boolTy, tyFun[boolTy, \
boolTy]]], p], q];
nat[n_] := Nest[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Num`sucConst[], #] &, \
HOL`Stdlib`Num`zeroConst[], n];
rnum[n_] := mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realOfRatConst[], \
mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Rat`ratOfIntConst[], mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Int`intOfNumConst[], \
nat[n]]]];
rLt[u_, v_] := mkComb[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realLtConst[], u], v];
rAdd[u_, v_] := mkComb[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realAddConst[], u], v];
rMul[u_, v_] := mkComb[mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realMulConst[], u], v];
rInv[u_] := mkComb[HOL`Stdlib`Real`realInvConst[], u];
a = mkVar[\"a\", realTy]; b = mkVar[\"b\", realTy];
midpoint = all[a, all[b, imp[rLt[a, b], rLt[a, rMul[rAdd[a, b], \
rInv[rnum[2]]]]]]];
formatThm[HOL`Auto`RealArith`realArithProve[midpoint]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"fed3d3cb-ff93-4cb3-a330-efe002eb5056"],

Cell["7. \[Dash] and the kernel will not be fooled", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ef7f65af-b9da-4942-87d9-1341ba9e45d4"],

Cell["\<\
The same prover refuses a false statement. Asked to prove  forall x y. x < y  \
it throws rather than return a theorem: that is the LCF trust boundary in \
action.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"04c08d5e-1680-44cb-9b5b-6c0e7ec03c4d"],

Cell["\<\
x = mkVar[\"x\", realTy]; y = mkVar[\"y\", realTy];
Catch[HOL`Auto`RealArith`realArithProve[all[x, all[y, rLt[x, y]]]], _,
  Function[{v, t}, \"refused: the prover threw rather than return a \
theorem\"]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"581220c2-535c-4f80-8662-6be1c881937d"],

Cell["Next steps", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"960e8a46-6d9c-47d8-8c75-c7cd32560047"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"README", ".", "md"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f492cad6-08be-4600-927e-16d437072cc3"],
 " for the project overview and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"docs", "/", 
   RowBox[{"USER_GUIDE", ".", "md"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f76b434-6d65-429f-9f37-4d07eb7b3705"],
 " for the API and how to develop your own proofs."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f0a2526e-b012-4934-9e22-98489c071773"]
},
WindowSize->{800, 700},
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Mac OS X x86 (64-bit) (2025\:5e747\:67088\:65e5)",
